</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crusaderdave>CrusaderDave</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 6:54:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26268.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:Problem</span><hr size=1> I think the idea of melee range nukes isn't a bad idea at all.  Here's what I'd do to make it work:<br>
<br>
They would have a very short range, if you try to cast it and you're out of range it would just give you the &quot;You're target it out of range&quot; message.  Which would prevent them from being used as soloing tools, you couldn't time it just right like PBAE kiting.<br>
<br>
To solve the aggro problem seems easy enough, just add a small concussion like effect to them.  Remember these are supposed to be group friendly, so adding this on the end of it would allow you to chain them quite well.  I'm not saying you should never get aggro, however.<br>
<br>
People are saying these type of spells would be too effective on raids, well then turn it off.  They have to code already in the game.  If you try to use pacify on something level 55+ you get the message, &quot;Your target seems uneffected by this spell&quot;  So SOE could add that onto whatever they didn't want effected by them.<br>
<br>
IMHO the way to make a spell line like this most effective would be something like this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Touch of Solusek<br>
Level 60<br>
Decrease Hitpoints by 500<br>
Lowers you on target's hate list by 50<br>
Mana: 100<br>
Casting time: 2.25 sec<br>
Recast: 2.25<br>
Resist check: Fire<br>
Range: 15 Feet</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Here's my thinking with the above suggestion.  Remember the goal of this of spells to encourage grouping.  A fast casting spell that helps maintain aggro, that has and excellent 5:1 ratio, but you have to be in melee range to use it.  15 feet is the same distance as most of the proc spells I noticed while I was looking through the spell list.  You would still have to controll your aggro, but chain casting with concussion after every couple of nukes and you'd be doing pretty good.<br>
<br>
Just some comparisions to help back up my suggestion:<br>
<br>
Ice Spear of Solist - 1200 / 300 = 4:1 ratio and 300 DPS<br>
Sunstrike - 1615 / 450 = 3.58:1 ratio and  230 DPS<br>
Garrison's Superior Sundering - 2100 / 540 = 3.88:1 ratio and 262.5 DPS<br>
Tears of Prexus - 2070 / 437 = 4.73:1 ratio and I'm not sure how to figure the dps because of the waves :P<br>
<br>
Touch of Solusek would be 500 / 100 = 5:1 ratio and 222.22 DPS<br>
<br>
BUT! You have to remember to add in the recast time which then brings the spell to a more humble 100 DPS.<br>
<br>
Why this makes sense to me:  For one just take a look at some of the weapons that melees can get hehe.  They can do insane damage forever as long as they still have hitpoints left.  What this spell represents is a way for a wizard to do more damage over the course of a mana bar, which they are still limited to unlike a rogue or other melee class.  Because of it's low casting time, this spell would not be affected by spell haste items/buffs.<br>
<br>
Anyways, the point of these type of spells would be to enable a wizard to continuously put up DPS like a melee, but we'd still be limited by mana, resists, and our own gimp HPS <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crusaderdave>CrusaderDave</A> at: 4/30/03 7:03:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tsurok@graffeswizardcompilation>Tsurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 7:04:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26268.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> The fix seems pretty simple to me even for PvP.  Reduce the effect diameter of the rain so that, for normal human-sized mobs, the max melee distance is greater than the rain effect diameter, sort of like how it is with giants now, i.e. melee won't get hit by rains if they stand back a little from giant-sized mobs, but can still melee.  Personally, I could care less about hitting multiple npcs with a rain and a good group should have no trouble keeping the mob stationary for the three waves.<br>
<br>
The drawbacks of a tighter diameter rain are obvious.  If the mob gets knocked around, aggros another in the group, or begins its death march, subsequent rains will not hit it.  To compensate for these...<br>
<br>
1)  Rains should have their damage scale up by level, like our DD's do.  This is a real problem with some rains for the less than lvl 50 crowd.<br>
2)  Rains should be affected by ID items.  <br>
3)  A wave which will kill an npc (or if they are in run mode, but snared)should have the same chance to hit as any other wave.<br>
<br>
-Tsu<br>
