-around anyway, and would be less than 100% as a fix.<br>
<br>
For PvP servers, they can simply add a check to see if a member is grouped - PBAoE spells already make this check, so I'm sure it wouldn't be too difficult to add the same check to rains.<br>
<br>
And the pre-50 rains are entirely useless.  They have ratios that are actually worse than same-level DDs, and that's before you take the ~20% resist rate into account.  If they had the same relative advantage over DDs (ratio-wise) that the post-50 rains do, that alone would go a long ways toward helping lower level wizards in groups.<br>
<br>
The post-50 rains are great though (and very group-friendly), and I use them whenever possible (and I'm on a PvP server!).   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tsurok@graffeswizardcompilation>Tsurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 10:15:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26268.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Agreed, flagging group members is a much better fix for pvp.  I didn't realize PBAOEs already did that for PvP.<br>
<br>
However, I think the radius on rains is pretty big.  A tighter radius would make it easier to use in tight quarters or with mez'd mobs in the camp.  I'd take it either way if SOE would only put a little time in to fix the quirky nature of rains and tweak them a little.<br>
<br>
I also agree RE: pre lvl 50 rains.  Those really need some help.<br>
